Package: RPyGeo
Type: Package
Title: ArcGIS Geoprocessing in R via Python
Version: 1.0.0
Date: 2018-03-07
Authors@R: c(
    person("Alexander", "Brenning", , "alexander.brenning@uni-jena.de", c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Fabian", "Polakowski", , "fabian.polakowski@gmail.com", role = "aut")
    )
Description: Provide access to (virtually any) ArcGIS Geoprocessing
        tool from within R by running Python geoprocessing scripts
        without writing Python code or touching ArcGIS.
        Requires ArcGIS >=10.0, a suitable version of Python
        (for ArcGIS 10.0: 2.6; for ArcGIS >= 10.1 : 2.7).
URL: https://github.com/fapola/RPyGeo
BugReports: https://github.com/fapola/RPyGeo/issues
License: GPL-3
LazyData: TRUE
Depends:
        dplyr
Imports:
        reticulate (>= 1.2),
        sf,
        raster,
        tools,
        stringr,
        utils,
        rmarkdown
SystemRequirements: Python (>= 2.6.0), ArcGIS (>= 10.0)
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
Suggests: testthat,
    knitr,
    spData,
    rstudioapi
VignetteBuilder: knitr
